cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a novel autoencoder model for feature learning in classification tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a multi-objective loss function and the incorporation of discriminability in the feature learning pipeline suggest the relevance of sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
